message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE. This paper is about a shared task on fine-grained propaganda detection, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with the study of computational models for various aspects of natural language processing. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which are all relevant to the task of developing effective models for propaganda detection.
